text:
According to the child's mother, when there was no resident biological father in the household (table 9) -40 percent of young children had contact with their father the same day as the home visit (when the parent interview was conducted);
-38 percent of children had contact with their father within 2 to 7 days of the home visit;
-7 percent of children had contact with their father within the last 8 to 14 days of the home visit;
-2 percent of children had not seen their father in more than 2 weeks; and -13 percent of children had never seen their father.
